cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper deals with transferring supervision between different modalities of images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses learned representations and proposes a new technique for pre-training, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of depth and optical flow images, which are commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems, indicating a possible fit for cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of pre-trained models for transfer learning, which is a common technique in multimedia analysis, suggesting a possible fit for cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
